          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px;">What is next for Bangladesh?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Bangladesh will face challenges in 2025. The provisional government led by Muhammed Yunnis will likely end, and the <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-dec-2024-8-elections" target="_blank">elections</a> are scheduled for later that year or early 2026. The upcoming national elections will be important in shaping the country's political stability and policy direction. The August ousting of the last PM could strain its relationship with India, one of its most potent economic and diplomatic partners. They have been asking India to return the ousted PM, Sheikh Hasina, so that she can <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-dec-2024-9-stand-trial" target="_blank">stand trial</a>. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The country is better positioned for stability than most post-regime change cases. A state structure is in place, large-scale ethnolinguistic issues are absent, and labor mobilization has not been a reason for political breakdown. But there are areas of concern including law and order breakdown, mobilization of anti-Hindu, anti-blasphemy sentiment, and the relationship between Islam and Bangladeshi nationalism.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Transparent political goals, economic reforms, punishments to the human rights abusers, complicated foreign policy environment with India, <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-dec-2024-10-civil-war" target="_blank">civil war</a> in Myanmar, and broader geopolitical issues involving the U.S. and China‚Äôs influence should be addressed in a limited period to ensure proper governance once Bangladesh picks its government. They must also confront climate change impacts like rising sea levels and frequent natural disasters, which demand innovative adaptation strategies. It also faces social challenges, such as improving education, healthcare, and poverty alleviation.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
