          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">On this day in 1065, the original <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-28-dec-2024-11-westminster-abbey" target="_blank">Westminister Abbey</a> was opened. In 1245, King Henry III decided to rebuild Westminster Abbey, tearing down the previous structure built by Edward the Confessor, except for the nave. He replaced it with the current abbey church, designed in the pointed Gothic style, which was popular then. Westminster Abbey is a UNESCO World Heritage site that has seen the crowing of every British sovereign except Edward V and Edward VIII. The site has also been a burial place for many British monarchs, poets, and politicians. Because of its beauty and historical significance, it attracts visitors worldwide.</p>
